### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@authToken = your_jwt_token_here
@refreshToken = your_refresh_token_here

### Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

### Login with email/password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

### Refresh access token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "refresh_token": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### Logout (requires authentication)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "refresh_token": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### Initiate Google OAuth Login
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/google

### Google OAuth Callback (this is handled automatically by the OAuth flow)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/google/callback

### Find User by ID (requires authentication)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/:id
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Find User by Email (requires authentication)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/email/:email
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

# Response Examples:

### Register Response
# {
#     "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
